<promed@promedmail.org>

[Exactly one year ago, on 30 Jan 2013, Lithuania's State Food and Veterinary Service (SFVS) performed a table-top simulation exercise on African swine fever in Vilnius. The exercise included theoretical and practical training of the personnel of SFVS with the aim of applying emergency measures in compliance with the contingency plans for the disease. It may be assumed -- but confirmation will be helpful -- that mass culling of wild boars was included among the considered contingency plans.

Further reading, with special reference to the vaccine issue, is available in the review:
Costard S, Wieland B, de Glanville W, et al: African swine fever: how can global spread be prevented? Philos Trans R Soc Lond B Biol Sci. 2009 Sep 27; 364(1530): 2683-96. doi: 10.1098/rstb.2009.0098; available at http://rstb.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/364/1530/2683.full.pdf. - Mod.AS]
